data.name: Content-Type
data.description: The Content-Type header MUST be set to application/pdf

data.name: X-Image-Quality
data.description: The resolution to downsample images to. Defaults to 72 ppi.
Reduce the size of scanned PDFs by shrinking image resolutions.
data.name: Compress a PDF file
quality
data.description: The resolution to downsample images to. Defaults to 72 ppi.

data.name: url
data.description: The URL of the PDF file to compress. If this parameter is used, a request will be made to the specified URL and the content returned for that request will be used as the data. The request MUST have a Content-Type header set to application/pdf. Alternatively, if the API request includes a Content-Type header set to application/pdf then the request body will be used as the contents of the file.

Creates an electronic book in either EPub or Kindle (.mobi) format.
data.name: Create Electronic Book
author
data.description: The author of the ebook.

data.name: content
data.description: The contents of the ebook. This is interpreted based on the datatype parameter. It can not be null or blank.

data.name: cover
data.description: The cover image for the ebook. It must be either a URL pointing to a JPEG file, or an actual JPEG file (as part of a multipart/form-data submission). Note that we do not validate the content type of the file: if it is not a JPEG then the book will be created but will fail to validate (for epub) and the cover won't be displayed.

data.name: css
data.description: Additional CSS style sheets for use with the ebook content. This is expected to be valid CSS and will be added to the ebook.

data.name: datatype
data.description: The type of content specified. Can be one of text/plain (plain text), text/html (HTML) or text/x-markdown (Markdown). Markdown will be run through a Markdown processor before the ebook is created, and plain text will be wrapped in an HTML <div> element.

data.name: enablechaptertitles
data.description: If false, disables the generation of chapter titles. By default, individual chapters within the book have titles.

data.name: format
data.description: The format of the ebook. If not present, an EPub file is returned. If set to mobi, a Kindle-compatible mobi file is returned.

data.name: lang
data.description: The 2-character language code for the book.

data.name: publisher
data.description: The name of the book's publisher.

data.name: title
data.description: This is the title of the ebook. It must be plain text, and it can not be null or blank.

Decodes the supplied barcode (from an PNG/GIF/JPEG image or a PDF file) and returns the barcode data. If decoding a PDF file an optional starting page number can be added to the end of the URL to specify which page to start searching for a barcode on (if not specified, the search begins on page 1 by default). Supported barcode formats are: QR, PDF417, DATAMATRIX, UPCA, UPCE, EAN13, EAN8, RSS14, RSSEXPANDED, CODE39, CODE93, CODE128, ITF, AZTEC, CODABAR, MAXICODE
data.name: Decode Barcode
debug
data.description: Requests the server emit additional logging detail to assist with troubleshooting.

data.name: url
data.description: The URL of the image or PDF file to extract a  barcode from. If this parameter is used, a request will be made to the specified URL and the Content-Type returned for that request will be used as the data type. Alternatively, if the API request includes a Content-Type header set to one of the acceptable formats (image/png, image/gif, image/jpg, image/jpeg, or application/pdf) then the request body will be used as the  contents of the file.
Returns the text in the selected PDF file, separated by page and display line.

data.name: Extract Text from PDF
url
data.description: The URL of the PDF file to extract text from. If this parameter is used, a request will be made to the specified URL and the content returned for that request will be used as the data. The request MUST have a Content-Type header set to application/pdf. Alternatively, if the API request includes a Content-Type header set to application/pdf then the request body will be used as the contents of the file.
Removes one or more pages from the specified PDF file.
data.name: Filter PDF Pages
pages
data.description: A JSON array with the page numbers to be removed. The page numbers must be integers, greater than  or equal to 1 and less than or equal to the total number of pages in the file. If passing the file using the POST body the page numbers can  be specified using the X-Parameter-Pages header.

data.name: url
data.description: The URL of the PDF file to filter specific pages from. If this parameter is used, a request will be made to the specified URL and the content returned for that request will be used as the data. The request MUST have a Content-Type header set to application/pdf. Alternatively, if the API request includes a Content-Type header set to application/pdf then the request body will be used as the contents of the file.
Generates a barcode from specified content and returns it as a PNG/GIF/JPEG image or a PDF file.
data.name: Generate Barcode
content
data.description: The content to encode in the barcode.

data.name: datatype
data.description: The mime-type of the output content. Supported formats include image/png (PNG), image/jpg  (JPEG), image/gif (GIF) and application/pdf (PDF).

data.name: errorcorrection
data.description: The type of error correction to use in the barcode. This  is only necessary if the barcode format supports it, and is ignored otherwise.

data.name: type
data.description: The type of barcode to generate.
data.value: QR, PDF417, DATAMATRIX, UPCA, UPCE, EAN13, RSS14, RSSEXPANDED, CODE39, CODE93, CODE128, ITF, AZTEC, CODABAR, MAXICODE

data.name: width
data.description: The width of the generated barcode. This is either a size in pixels or a size constant (for example L, S, or M for QR codes).

Obtain one or more thumbnail images representing the pages of a PDF file. If a single page is requested it will be returned as a PNG image. If multiple pages are requested then a ZIP file will be returned (with the Content-Type header of the response set to application/zip), and each image within the zip file will be named with the page number (for example, 1.png, 2.png etc).
data.name: Get Thumbnails
pages
data.description: This can either be the string "all" (for all pages) or a JSON array with the specific page numbers. If using the JSON argument the page numbers must be integers, greater than  or equal to 1 and less than or equal to the total number of pages in the file. If passing the file using the POST body the page numbers can  be specified using the X-Parameter-Pages header.

data.name: url
data.description: The URL of the PDF file to obtain thumbnails from. If this parameter is used, a request will be made to the specified URL and the content returned for that request will be used as the data. The request MUST have a Content-Type header set to application/pdf. Alternatively, if the API request includes a Content-Type header set to application/pdf then the request body will be used as the contents of the file.
Joins 2 or more PDF files into a single PDF file.
data.name: Join PDF Files
document
data.description: The URL of each PDF file to be merged: this parameter can be supplied multiple times. The merged PDF file will contain the pages of all the supplied files in the order the arguments are specified. If the Content-Type header is set to application/x-www-form-urlencoded then the parameter values will be expected to be URLs: a request will be made to each specified URL and the content returned for those requests will be used for the merge. The content returned MUST have a Content-Type header set to application/pdf. Alternatively, if the API request includes a Content-Type header set to multipart/form-data then the request body will be expected to contain each of the files to be merged.
Adds password encryption and access permissions to a specific file. Currently only supports RC4 encryption.
data.name: Lock PDF File
displaypassword
data.description: The display password to be applied to the file. If this is not set then the file can be opened without presenting any password. If passing the file using the POST body the display password can be specified using the X-Parameter-DisplayPassword header.

data.name: encryptionlength
data.description: Set to 40 to use 40-bit RC4 encryption, compatible with Adobe Acrobat 3 and higher. By default (if this parameter is not specified), 128-bit RC4 encryption is used (compatible with Adobe Acrobat 5 and higher). If passing the file using the POST body the X-Parameter-EncryptionLength request header can be passed with the encryption value.

data.name: permissions
data.description: A JSON array with the permissions to be configured for the user password. If this parameter is missing or is an empty array then no permissions are specified and all actions are disabled for anyone viewing the file with the user password.  If passing the file using the POST body the permissions can be passed using the X-Parameter-Permissions header. Supported permissions are  annotations (permit a non-owner to add/modify text annotations and fill in form fields), assemble (permit a non-owner to insert/delete/reposition pages), extract (permit a non-owner to extract text and images), extractaccessibility (permit a non-owner to extract text and images for accessibility purposes), fillform (permit a non-owner to fill in form fields), modify (permit a non-owner to modify the document), print (permit a non-owner to print the document in a degraded format), and printhigh (permit a non-owner to print the document at the highest available fidelity).

data.name: permissionspassword
data.description: The permissions password to be applied to the file. If passing the file using the POST body the permissions password can be specified using the X-Parameter-PermissionsPassword header.

data.name: url
data.description: The URL of the PDF file to encrypt. If this parameter is used, a request will be made to the specified URL and the content returned for that request will be used as the data. The request MUST have a Content-Type header set to application/pdf. Alternatively, if the API request includes a Content-Type header set to application/pdf then the request body will be used as the contents of the file. Only RC4 encryption is currently supported.
Draws a simple bar chart based on the g.raphael library and return a PNG or PDF version of the chart.
data.name: Render Bar Chart
backgroundcolor
data.description: The background color to use on the chart. Defaults to white (#ffffff).

data.name: bartype
data.description: The edge detail on the bars: can be one of soft, sharp, round, square. Defaults to  square.

data.name: color
data.description: The color(s) to be used for the chart. For a single series, you can pass a single color. For stacked or multi-series charts, pass an array of color values that is the same length as the values parameter.

data.name: datatype
data.description: The mime-type of the output content. Supported formats include image/png (PNG), and application/pdf (PDF).

data.name: dpi
data.description: The pixel density of the output image (for raster formats). Defaults to 90dpi.

data.name: height
data.description: The height of the generated chart. This is a size in pixels.

data.name: horizontal
data.description: If present, the chart will be horizontal. By default, the chart is vertical.

data.name: stacked
data.description: If present, the chart will be stacked. By default, the chart is not stacked.

data.name: title
data.description: (Not used) The chart title. Will be used in a future release.

data.name: values
data.description: The values to be charted. For a single series, pass a JSON array with numeric values. For stacked or multi-series charts, pass a JSON array where each member is also an array of numeric values: the members must all be the same length.

data.name: width
data.description: The width of the generated chart. This is a size in pixels.
Creates a gauge chart and returns a PNG or PDF version of the chart.
data.name: Render Gauge
datatype
data.description: The mime-type of the output content. Supported formats include image/png (PNG), and application/pdf (PDF).

data.name: dpi
data.description: The pixel density of the output image (for raster formats). Defaults to 90dpi.

data.name: gaugebackgroundcolor
data.description: The background color to be used on the gauge line.

data.name: gradient
data.description: Set to false to use a sector-based colors for the gauge: green if the value is less than 33% of the max, yellow if it is less than 66% of the max, and red otherwise. Defaults to true, which selects a gauge color based on the percentage of the maximum value, instead of a range.

data.name: height
data.description: The height of the generated chart. This is a size in pixels.

data.name: label
data.description: The label to be placed under the gauge value. Defaults to a blank label.

data.name: max
data.description: The maximum value of the gauge.

data.name: min
data.description: The minimum value of the gauge.

data.name: title
data.description: The title of the gauge chart. Defualts to a blank title.

data.name: value
data.description: The current value of the gauge.

data.name: width
data.description: The width of the generated chart. This is a size in pixels.

backgroundcolor
data.description: The background color to use on the chart. Defaults to white (#ffffff).

data.name: color
data.description: The color(s) to be used for the chart. For a single series, you can pass a single color. For multi-series charts, pass an array of color values that is the same length as the xvalues parameter.

data.name: datatype
data.description: The mime-type of the output content. Supported formats include image/png (PNG), and application/pdf (PDF).

data.name: dpi
data.description: The pixel density of the output image (for raster formats). Defaults to 90dpi.

data.name: height
data.description: The height of the generated chart. This is a size in pixels.

data.name: title

data.name: width
data.description: The width of the generated chart. This is a size in pixels.

data.name: xvalues
data.description: The x-axis values to be charted. Must be a JSON array with numeric values.

data.name: yvalues
data.description: The y-axis values to be charted. For a single series, pass a JSON array with numeric values that is the same length as the xvalues parameters. For multi-series charts, pass a JSON array where each member is also an array of numeric values: the members must all be the same length as the xvalues parameter..
Removes all password encryption and access permissions from a PDF file. Currently only supports RC4 encryption.
data.name: Unlock PDF File
password
data.description: The owner password to use when decrypting the file. If passing the file using the POST body the owner password can be specified using the X-Parameter-Password header.

data.name: url
data.description: The URL of the PDF file to decrypt. If this parameter is used, a request will be made to the specified URL and the content returned for that request will be used as the data. The request MUST have a Content-Type header set to application/pdf. Alternatively, if the API request includes a Content-Type header set to application/pdf then the request body will be used as the contents of the file. Only RC4 encryption is currently supported.

description:
Textibility provides a simple, REST API for extracting information from images and documents in a number of formats and generating images and documents from structured data. With a simple, clean HTTP interface and some clever processing we can quickly and easily unlock information captured in photographs and file uploads.
A couple of examples supported by the API:

    Decode a barcode from a photograph.
    Generating a barcode for a product (UPC), a boarding pass (PDF417) or to point to a URL or describe a contact (QR).
    Generate an EPub or Kindle-compatible electronic book.
    Generate static charts.
